{
  "stem": "2723.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And my mother had a note smuggled in to her by someone which said that the outside part of the family managed to persuade the powers to be, probably with heavy financial help, to get us out.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we were also told that a dignitary, Slovak dignitary, was coming to inspect the camp.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And he will be calling out the names of those that will be released.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "My mother drilled Vera and I how to behave, that we were to hold her hands, and we will be called.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And we just, as quietly as we can, have to leave.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "When the moment came-- and outside that building there were railway lines.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It was a, disused until then, railway siding.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And the wagons were ready to take the first lot of Jews away.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "The men came in and after a few charming words, which you can imagine, he called the Jewess Elizabeth Silberstein, and the Jewess Eva, and the Jewess Vera, at which point my mother, holding our hands, wanted to yank us forward.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And another woman with two children stepped up too.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "There was a momentary confusion.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And it was our luck that the office bearer who came to inspect, who was the minister for the interior, wanted this confusion clarified.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And it transpired that a Jewish person, a go between with the Germans, sold our release papers to another woman with two children for more money, and was quite morally prepared to let us go to the wagons.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And I think the shock horror of that suddenly made me grow up properly.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "I realized then that the situation was hopeless.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "If one of us became such scum, there was very little to hope for.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "We were, however, released.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
